Q9: I think it would be good if the software could recognize synonyms as you are typing. For someone like me who is just introduced to systematics it would be helpful if the system asked "do you mean stems" when trying to search for culm length, for example. Then you don't have to start making a new character just to find out that there was a synonym. It would save time for people who don't know all the terminology yet.

Q9: The instructions were very clear and the tutorial helped a lot. I have no complaints
Q10: I really liked the suggestions, the tags, the synonyms, the recommendations, the database of similar adjectives and descriptions... I really think this will be useful for unifying Carex descriptions so that it is clearer and clearer what is the same, what is similar, and what is different. This is a hefty task in the vein of Linnaeus who wanted to boil down all the long descriptive polynomial names into genus+species.

Q9:
The export option to receive a ZIP file did not always work. Another annoyance I had was that while CR does tell you if a synonymous character exists via a pop-up, I feel like when you type in the synonym, it should appear in the drop down menu. 

Additionally, it was very annoying that the test matrix kept asking to be renamed. Just having a "save" option or "discard changes" would be nice.
Q10:
I do like the pictures describing each character. Very useful for new users and those unfamiliar with the genus' characteristics. I also like how there is autosuggestion of descriptive characters, though the human imagination is endless so I hope that works out. 

I also like how parts of the plant i.e., leaf, stem, inflorescence unit were separated into tabs! Very nice and organized.
